{"word":"H6924 - קֶדֶם - qedem - keh'-dem - Aforetime","slug":"H6924","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">קֶדֶם</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>qedem"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>keh'-dem"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Aforetime"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E7;&#x05D3;&#x05DE;&#x05D4;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05E7;&#x05D3;&#x05DD; - qedem  qe&#x0302;dma&#x0302;h</b> - <i>keh'-dem, kayd'-maw</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H6923\">H6923</a>; the <i>front</i>, of palce (absolutely the <i>fore part</i>, relatively the <i>East</i>) or time (<i>antiquity</i>); often used adverbially (<i>before</i>, <i>anciently</i>, <i>eastward</i>): - aforetime, ancient (time), before, east (end, part, side, -ward), eternal, X ever (-lasting), forward, old, past. Compare <a href=\"#/H6926\">H6926</a>."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H6917\">H6917</a>, <a href=\"#/H6921\">H6921</a>, <a href=\"#/H6923\">H6923</a>, <a href=\"#/H6926\">H6926</a>, <a href=\"#/H6927\">H6927</a>, <a href=\"#/H6929\">H6929</a>, <a href=\"#/H6930\">H6930</a>, <a href=\"#/H6931\">H6931</a>, <a href=\"#/H6932\">H6932</a>, <a href=\"#/H6934\">H6934</a>, <a href=\"#/H6935\">H6935</a>"}]}